7 They have Princely Company;
                  7 They have Princely Company. God himſelf the Father, Son, and Holy Ghoſt, having communion with them. We write theſe things to you (ſaith the Apoſtle) that ye may have fellowſhip with us, and truly our fellowſhip is with the father, and the Son, and the holy Ghoſt, 1 John 1.3. 2 Cor. 13.14. And is not here good company? Chriſt comes in to his people, and ſups with them, and they with him, Rev. 3.20. He will manifeſt himſelf, and not leave them comfortleſſe, but will come to them, John 14.18, 21. They have alſo the Company of the glorious Angels, who are Princes, Dan. 10.13. And of the ſpirits of juſt men made perfect, Heb. 12.23. Behold all that are of this company are Kings and Queens, a Senate of

Kings, as it was ſaid of the Roman Councel.
